ES

TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Montreux-Palace Hotel

1820 Montreux, Switzerland

March 3, 1976

Dear Mr. Oakes,

I thank you for your kind letter. Yes, the Alpine choughs still walk at dawn on my window-sill, making kissing sounds.

The pictures by Ovenden1 of that young sea-cow posing as my Lolita are, of course, preposterous, and the Academy Editions' plan to publish them has not received my blessing. Yet there is nothing much I can do about it. Recently I was shown an advert in an American rag of